The argument Nintendo used was 'fraud' because when a
non-authorized cart was inserted the screen would still
say 'an official licensed game from Nintendo.'  The
cart makers acknowledge that they put a magic bytes where
they were expected, but that it was the CPU and the logic inside
the box that was displaying the message, not them.
